<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id065d461c-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d" identifier="/us/usc/t19/s4662"><num value="4662">§ 4662.</num><heading> Duties</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The duties described in this section are the following:</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id065d461d-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d" identifier="/us/usc/t19/s4662/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> Assisting the Interagency Labor Committee to monitor and enforce the labor obligations of Mexico.</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id065d461e-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d" identifier="/us/usc/t19/s4662/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> Submitting to the Interagency Labor Committee on a quarterly basis reports on the efforts undertaken by Mexico to comply with its labor obligations.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="id065d461f-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d">(<ref href="/us/pl/116/113/tVII/s722">Pub. L. 116–113, title VII, § 722</ref>, <date date="2020-01-29">Jan. 29, 2020</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/134/86">134 Stat. 86</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
